She says that the procedure is "painful but positive".
We are in the process of cleaning up the wound, but we would need an investigative unit dedicated solely to Montreal, as well as supervision, in order to prevent a return to the questionable practices.
How to clean.
Regularly.
For his part, Jacques Duchesneau notes that 'officials have stolen several hundred million dollars', but above all he is concerned about the role of 'elected officials who know the tactics' when they were not involved in the fraud!
Starting with a 70% share of black money in funding Quebec ’ s election campaigns, he quips, “I ’ ve been told it ’ s a faint imitation of reality. ”
The Quebec government proposes to limit donations to political parties to 100 dollars, which, according to him, would not change the situation: "As long as campaign expenditure is not strictly limited, black money will circulate in politics."
He recommends a complete overhaul of the system for awarding public contracts and funding the parties: 'We cannot go deeper; by getting to the bottom of things with courage, we can rebuild the house on a more solid basis with more controls and laws.'
If this story damages the international reputation of Quebec and Montreal, Mr. Duchesneau invites those who laugh at it to take a look into their own backyard...
