Larry Hagman, whose role as the oil magnate J.R. Ewing in the television series "Dallas" became a symbol of greed in the 80s, is dead.
He was 81 years old.
Hagman, who returned this year as J.R. in a new season of "Dallas", died Friday afternoon due to cancer complications according to a family press release to The Associated Press by Warner Bros., producer of "Dallas".
"Larry was back in his beloved native Dallas, where he once again played the iconic role he liked most," the family said.
Larry ’ s family and his closest friends were with him in Dallas to celebrate Thanksgiving.
Linda Gray, who played the role of his wife in the original and subsequent series, was with Hagman when he died in the Dallas hospital, her publicist Jeffrey Lane said.
